               <p>MR. ADOLPHUS conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-158-person919">
                  JOHN 
                  GODFREY
               <interp inst="t18280911-158-person919" type="surname" value="GODFREY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person919" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person919" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am <rs id="t18280911-158-viclabel800" type="occupation">Ordinance store-keeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-158-victim918 t18280911-158-viclabel800"></join> at Purfleet. On the 5th of August I was in the <placeName id="t18280911-158-crimeloc801">Tower of London</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-158-crimeloc801" type="placeName" value="Tower of London"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-158-crimeloc801" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-158-off798 t18280911-158-crimeloc801"></join> - a person gave me some information; I looked round, and saw the two prisoners near me: Jones lifted his hat from off his head, and my handkerchief fell from it; he said "It fell from the gentleman's pocket;" this is it - I did not see either of the prisoners do anything to me; there was no crowd about.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-158-person920">
                  RICHARD 
                  THROP
               <interp inst="t18280911-158-person920" type="surname" value="THROP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person920" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person920" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was near the Record-office in the Tower on the 5th of August; I saw the two prisoners go behind the prosecutor - Jones helf up his pocket while Smith took the handkerchief out, and gave it to Jones, who put it into his hat; I told the prosecutor of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-158-person921">
                  JOHN 
                  HOPKINS
               <interp inst="t18280911-158-person921" type="surname" value="HOPKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person921" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-person921" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am one of the warders of the Tower. I took the prisoners into custody.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>SMITH'S Defence. I saw the handkerchief on the ground; I took it up; the other prisoner said "It dropped from the gentleman's coat pocket;" I said, "Are you sure of that?" he said Yes; I gave it to him to give to the gentleman: we were taken to Lambeth-street, and there the witness swore that Jones held the pocket and I took the handkerchief, but I am quite innocent.</p>
               <p>SMITH - <rs id="t18280911-158-verdict802" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-verdict802" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
               <p>JONES - <rs id="t18280911-158-verdict803" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-158-verdict803" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
